					<p><strong>The Panini Super Bowl Kid Reporter Promotion Official Rules<br>
					No Purchase Necessary to Enter or Win.</strong></p>
					<p><strong>1. Eligibility:</strong> The Panini Super Bowl Kid Reporter Promotion (hereafter, "Promotion") is open to legal residents of the fifty (50) United States and the District of Columbia who are 18 years of age or older and a parent or legal guardian of a minor child who is a legal U.S. resident between the ages of 7 and 13 years old as of 4/18/16. Employees, officers, directors, representatives and agents of Panini America, Inc. ("Sponsor"), NFL Properties LLC, the NFL Parties (defined as NFL Enterprises LLC, NFL Properties LLC, the National Football League, its member professional football clubs, NFL Ventures, Inc., NFL Ventures, L.P., NFL International LLC, NFL Productions LLC, teamDigital Promotions, Inc. ("Promotion Agency") and each of their respective parent companies, subsidiaries, affiliates, governors, owners, distributors, retailers, franchisees, and advertising and promotion agencies (collectively "Released Parties") and the immediate family members (parent, spouse, sibling or child, and their respective spouses, regardless of where they reside) and those living in the same household of each, whether or not related, are not eligible to participate or win. Void where prohibited or restricted by law, rule or regulation. This Promotion is subject to all applicable federal, state, and local laws.</p>

					<p><strong>2. Promotion Period and Dates:</strong>  The Promotion will consist of two (2) components: a contest ("Contest") and a sweepstakes ("Sweepstakes"). The Sweepstakes Entry Period starts at 12:00:01PM Eastern Time ("ET") on 4/18/16 and ends at 11:59:59PM ET on 1/8/17 ("Sweepstakes Entry Period"). The Contest Period starts at 12:00:01PM ET on 1/9/17 and ends at 11:59:59 PM ET on 1/15/17 ("Contest Period"). The Sweepstakes will be divided into ten (10) Finalist Prize Drawings, nine (9) Monthly Prize Drawings, and thirty-eight (38) Weekly Prize Drawings.</p>

					<p><strong>3. To Obtain An Access Code to Participate in the Sweepstakes:</strong> You may obtain an access code needed to participate in the Sweepstakes (as outlined below), in one of two (2) ways: 1) Purchase select Panini NFL Trading Card products between 4/18/16 and 12/30/16 (or while supplies last); or 2) To obtain an access code and Official Rules without making a purchase send a self addressed stamped envelope (VT residents may omit return stamp) to be received by 1/4/17 to: Panini Super Bowl Kid Reporter Code Request, 5325 FAA Blvd, Suite 100, Irving, TX 75061. Limit one access code request per stamped outer mailing envelope, mailed separately. Access codes that are fraudulent, tampered with or obtained through unauthorized channels will be void.</p>

					<p><strong>4. How to Participate in the Sweepstakes:</strong> During the Promotion Period, visit <a href="http://www.PaniniKidReporter.com">www.PaniniKidReporter.com</a> and follow the instructions provided to enter your access code and to fully complete and submit the registration form to earn one entry into the Sweepstakes. Registration is free. Each access code may only be entered one (1) time. The use of script, macro or automated devices (or any other devices intended to automate any aspect of participation) to enter is prohibited.  If Released Parties, in their sole discretion, determines that an entrant has used an automated or similar device to play or is in violation of these Official Rules, all entries from that entrant or email address will be void. In the event of a dispute as to the identity of an entrant based on the email address submitted, entry will be awarded to the person named on the applicable registration form (regardless of whether that is the name of the authorized account holder of the email address from which said registration was submitted) and he/she must comply with these Official Rules. Released Parties are not responsible for late, lost, stolen, incomplete, misdirected, delayed, garbled, inaccurate, or undelivered Access Codes, registrations, or for telephonic, human or computer failures, problems or errors, interruptions in service due to system upgrades, repairs, modifications or other causes, failures or malfunctions of connections, satellite, network, cable, Internet Service Provider (ISP), phones, phone lines or telephone systems, traffic congestion on the internet, technical or mechanical malfunctions, or other malfunctions or errors, whether caused by equipment, programming, human error or otherwise relating to or in connection with the Sweepstakes, including, without limitation, errors which may occur in connection with the administration of the Sweepstakes, the announcement of the prizes, any injury or damage to participant’s or any other person’s computer relating to or resulting from participation in this Sweepstakes, the failure of any specially marked Panini products to contain an Access Code, in any Sweepstakes-related materials, for any travel delays or cancellations, or for printing, typographical, human or other errors appearing in these Official Rules or other Sweepstakes-related materials.</p>

